<http://model.geneontology.org/69b3372b00002198> <http://geneontology.org/lego/modelstate> "development"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/pav/providedBy> "https://syngo.vu.nl"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <http://model.geneontology.org/69b3372b00002198> ;
	<https://w3id.org/biolink/vocab/in_taxon> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom> <http://model.geneontology.org/6994852c00002231> ;
	a <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Edge: PPP3CA -> PPP1CA | Relation: positively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: pharmacol (FK506) | Assay: SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 4G | Note: PP2B acts partly upstream of PP1; FK506 partially blocks NMDA-induced STG dephosphorylation"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: DLG4 -> CACNG2 | Relation: directly positively regulates | PMID: 15664178, 17346965 | Model: rat/hippocampal slice culture, rat/dissociated hippocampal neurons, COS-7 cells | Perturbation: mut (S9D-delta4), mut (ΔC), mut (T321F/H225V compensatory pair) | Assay: paired whole-cell recording, single quantum dot tracking, mEPSC recording, co-clustering in COS-7 | Fig: Tomita 3E, Bats 2B-C, 6B-E, S3, S8 | Note: PSD-95 PDZ domain binding is required for CACNG2's synaptic receptor adaptor activity. Tomita: S9D-delta4 (phosphomimic without PDZ site) depresses AMPA EPSC instead of enhancing it (Fig 3E). Bats: ΔC drops mEPSC frequency from 1.14 to 0.04 Hz (Fig 2B-C); StargazinT321F alone drops AMPAR immobilization to 10%, rescued to 69% by compensatory PSD-95 H225V (Fig 6B); StargazinT321F only localizes to synapses when compensatory PSD-95 is present (Fig S8). PSD-95 turnover (~25% over 5 min) is much slower than Stargazin (~25% in 30s), indicating the Stargazin-PSD-95 dissociation is the rate-limiting step for AMPAR synaptic exit."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: PPP1CA -> CACNG2 | Relation: directly negatively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: pharmacol (tautomycin) | Assay: SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 4F | Note: PP1 mediates NMDA-induced STG dephosphorylation; tautomycin completely blocks it; Ca2+-dependent"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: IQSEC1 -> ARF6 | Relation: directly positively regulates | PMID: 20510858 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, HEK293 cells (transfected), rat/hippocampal neuron cultures | Perturbation: mut (E604K catalytically inactive), KD (lentiviral RNAi), pharmacol (PP2 src inhibitor, OV/PAO tyrosine phosphatase inhibitors) | Assay: in vitro nucleotide exchange assay, Arf6-GTP pull-down (cellular) | Fig: 3A-D, 4A-C, 5C-D | Note: GluA2-CT stimulates BRAG2 GEF activity on Arf6 ~5-fold in vitro; this stimulation requires intact 3Y motif and unphosphorylated Y876 (Fig 3A-D). In HEK293 cells, glutamate and CNQX (partial agonist) both trigger BRAG2-dependent Arf6 activation (Fig 4A-B). In neurons, DHPG activates Arf6 via tyrosine dephosphorylation; this is blocked by BRAG2 RNAi and by tyrosine phosphatase inhibitors OV/PAO (Fig 5C-D). Src inhibitor PP2 alone activates Arf6 by releasing Y876 phosphorylation brake (Fig 4C)."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: IQSEC1 -> GRIA2 | Relation: directly negatively regulates | PMID: 20510858 | Model: rat/hippocampal neuron cultures | Perturbation: KD (lentiviral RNAi), mut (E604K catalytically inactive), mut (Arf6-T44N constitutively inactive), pharmacol (NBQX AMPAR antagonist) | Assay: surface biotinylation, cell ELISA, reversible surface biotinylation (endocytosis assay) | Fig: 6A-F | Note: BRAG2 RNAi prevents DHPG-induced reduction of surface GluA2 (cell ELISA Fig 6A, surface biotinylation Fig 6B). Catalytically inactive BRAG2 E604K blocks both surface reduction and endocytosis of GluA2 (Fig 6C,F). Constitutively inactive Arf6-T44N also blocks surface reduction (Fig 6D). NBQX prevents DHPG-induced surface reduction, confirming AMPAR ligand binding is required (Fig 6E). None of these manipulations affect basal surface GluA2 levels."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: GRIA2 -> IQSEC1 | Relation: directly positively regulates | PMID: 20510858 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, HEK293 cells | Perturbation: mut (GluA2 Y876A, Y876F, V875Y/Y876V, Δ3Y), phosphorylation (src kinase in vitro, PP2/OV/PAO in cells) | Assay: in vitro nucleotide exchange assay, Arf6-GTP pull-down (cellular) | Fig: 3A-D, 4A-B | Note: GluA2 C-terminus directly stimulates BRAG2 GEF activity ~5-fold via 3Y motif binding to Sec7-PH module (Fig 3A). Y876A and V875Y/Y876V abolish stimulation; Y876F preserves it (Fig 3A). Phosphorylation of Y876 by src blocks stimulation; phosphatase treatment restores it (Fig 3C-D). AMPAR ligand binding (glutamate, CNQX) in HEK293 cells triggers BRAG2-dependent Arf6 activation, showing that conformational change from ligand binding is transmitted to C-tail for BRAG2 activation (Fig 4A-B). This is a \"dual key\" mechanism: both ligand binding AND Y876 dephosphorylation required."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Node: IQSEC1 | UniProt: Q6DN90 | PMID: 20510858 | Model: yeast two-hybrid, HEK293 cells (transfected), rat/hippocampal neuron cultures, mouse/hippocampal slices (acute, in vivo lentiviral injection), Iqsec1fl/fl conditional KO mice, purified recombinant proteins | Perturbation: KD (lentiviral RNAi, two independent shRNAs), KO (Cre-lox conditional, Iqsec1fl/fl), mut (E604K catalytically inactive), competing peptide (GST-3Y vs GST-3Y-V875Y/Y876V) | Assay: yeast two-hybrid, GST pull-down, co-immunoprecipitation, in vitro nucleotide exchange assay, Arf6-GTP pull-down (cellular), surface biotinylation, cell ELISA, reversible surface biotinylation (endocytosis), whole-cell patch clamp (LTD recording), subcellular fractionation, Western blot | Fig: 1A-E, 2A-C, 3A-D, 4A-C, 5A-D, 6A-F, 7A-C, 8A-B | Note: BRAG2 is a synaptic Arf6-GEF concentrated in PSD fractions that directly binds GluA2 via the 3Y motif (YKEGYNVY876G) through its Sec7-PH module (Y2H, GST pull-down, co-IP; Fig 1A-E). GluA2 C-terminus stimulates BRAG2 GEF activity ~5-fold in vitro, controlled by Y876 phosphorylation state — dephosphorylated Y876 permits activation, phosphorylation blocks it (Fig 3A-D). AMPAR ligand binding (glutamate or CNQX) triggers BRAG2-dependent Arf6 activation in HEK293 cells and neurons (Fig 4A-C). BRAG2 is required for both mGluR-LTD and NMDAR-LTD — RNAi, conditional KO, catalytically inactive mutant, and competing 3Y peptide all block LTD expression without affecting initial DHPG-induced depression (Fig 6A-F, 7A-C, 8A-B)."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: PRKCA -> CACNG2 | Relation: directly positively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: none (in vitro), pharmacol (GF109203X, cellular) | Assay: in vitro kinase assay (direct), SDS-PAGE mobility shift (cellular) | Fig: 5B-C | Note: Direct phosphorylation of STG tail in vitro (more efficient than histone); confirmed in neurons where GF109203X blocks rephosphorylation after NMDA washout"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Node: ATAD1 | UniProt: Q8NBU5 | PMID: 21496646 | Model: Mus musculus, primary mouse hippocampal neurons, primary mouse cortical neurons, HEK293 cells | Perturbation: Knockout (conditional genetic deletion), overexpression (lentiviral transduction), missense mutations (Walker A K193T, Walker B E139Q), TTX treatment, bicuculline treatment | Assay: Immunoblot, subcellular fractionation, co-immunoprecipitation, GST-pull down, surface biotinylation, live-cell immunohistochemistry, whole-cell patch-clamp, behavioral assays | Fig: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 | Note: Thorase (ATAD1) is a postsynaptically enriched AAA+ ATPase that regulates synaptic plasticity, learning, and memory. It critically controls the surface expression and endocytosis of AMPA receptors (AMPARs) through an ATPase-dependent mechanism, where its deletion leads to increased surface AMPAR levels, enhanced LTP, eliminated LTD, and severe behavioral deficits."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title> """NMDAR-dependent recruitment of AMPA receptor to clathrin adaptor complex - Mouse
"""^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> "https://orcid.org/0009-0005-9047-3868"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date> "2026-03-24"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .

